<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-06T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-06T07:00:00-05:00" n="428" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d428">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War, 1939/166:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-06T15:00:00+03:00">September
                                    6, 1939—3 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received September 6—10:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>514. I am reliably informed that in a recent interview between the Polish
                            Ambassador and Molotov<note n="32" xml:id="d428fn32">Vyacheslav M.
                                Molotov, Chairman of the Council of People’s Commissars of the
                                Soviet Union.</note> the latter expressed surprise that England and
                            France had actually declared war on Germany.</p>
                        <p>I also understand that although the Polish Ambassador endeavored to
                            obtain from Molotov a clarification of the Soviet attitude towards the
                            Polish-German conflict Molotov was non-committal and evasive.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>